<div><div class="article-detail-container w-container"><div class="news-detail-article-block"><div class="w-richtext">
<p>‍</p>
<p>‍</p>
<p>‍</p>
<h1>‍</h1>
<h1>Childcare for Children of Healthcare and Emergency Workers</h1>
<p>Please use the link below to register for Emergency Workers Childcare through March 27, 2020.</p>
<p><a href="https://forms.gle/JfKiqhVRTBiEADp49" target="_blank">https://forms.gle/JfKiqhVRTBiEADp49</a><br></p>
<p>More information will be sent for eLearning childcare in the next week.</p>
<p>‍</p>
<h1>Lunches for ISLA Families</h1>
<p>Starting March 18-April 3, parents can visit any of the six elementary schools in the Hopkins District from 11:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m. The bagged meal option will include a lunch and next-day breakfast. Please note: This is a pick-up location only. Students will not be able to eat meals inside school per the guidelines provided by the CDC and the Minnesota Department of Health regarding social distancing.</p>
<p>Students may pick up meals on their own and parents may pick up meals for their children.</p>
<p>Here are the addresses for the Hopkins Schools:</p>
<p>Alice Smith Elementary – 801 Minnetonka Mills Road Hopkins, MN 55343<br>Eisenhower Elementary – 1001 Highway 7 Hopkins, MN 55305<br>Gatewood Elementary – 14900 Gatewood Drive Minnetonka, MN 55345<br>Glen Lake Elementary – 4801 Woodridge Road, Minnetonka, MN 55345<br>L.H. Tanglen Elementary – 10901 Hillside Lane, Minnetonka, MN 55305<br>Meadowbrook Elementary – 5430 Glenwood Avenue, Golden Valley, MN 55422</p>
<p>Bus stop meal drop off for students who don’t live close to an elementary school:</p>
<p>Hopkins transportation department will route school buses to reach students that would otherwise be unable to walk to an elementary school in the Hopkins District. The link below will help you find a stop close to your home. You may also call Hopkins transportation at 952-988-4116 to find the closest stop.</p>
<p>Please arrive 5 minutes before the time listed to obtain a lunch/breakfast bag.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.hopkinsschools.org/sites/default/files/public/meal_route_bus_info_03-19-20.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.hopkinsschools.org/sites/default/files/public/meal_route_bus_info_03-19-20.pdf</a></p>
<p>More information regarding student meals for April will be sent at a later date.</p>
<p>If your employment or income status has been effected by COVID – 19, we strongly encourage you to apply for meal benefits today. Here is the link for an application.</p>
<p>English – <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B9h5nmi1k7ZMRl9HRjY5bVZtNjUtMHZRcGZ0dkI1ZUp3NWU4/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank">https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B9h5nmi1k7ZMRl9HRjY5bVZtNjUtMHZRcGZ0dkI1ZUp3NWU4/view?usp=sharing</a></p>
<p>Spanish - <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B9h5nmi1k7ZMdlFobWF6cFU0VUpMeVY5QkhwWDZKOUxwTE5F/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank">https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B9h5nmi1k7ZMdlFobWF6cFU0VUpMeVY5QkhwWDZKOUxwTE5F/view?usp=sharing</a></p>
<p>‍</p>
<p>‍</p>
<h1>Food Baskets for ISLA Familes</h1>
<p>On Monday, March 23rd - 25th, we will start collecting non-perishable food items for pick up by our families in need. If you would like to donate, there will be bins/boxes for drop off in the ISLA lobby. Families can pick up these items on Thursday, March 26th in the ISLA lobby. Here are a list of items needed:</p>
<ul>
<li>Breakfast cereal (including oatmeal)</li>
<li>Rice</li>
<li>Beans</li>
<li>Canned meats (chicken, tuna, ham)</li>
<li>Canned fruit (in juice)</li>
<li>Canned vegetables</li>
<li>Soup (all kinds)</li>
<li>Boxed meals</li>
<li>Pasta</li>
<li>Canned tomatoes (sauce, paste, diced, etc)</li>
<li>Bottled or canned juice</li>
</ul>
<p>Unfortunately, we cannot accept fresh food items, milk, eggs, cheese or any item that is perishable.</p>
<p>Thank you in advance for helping to take care of our ISLA community!</p>
